The paper deals with routing algorithms in computer networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the theory of collective intelligence (COIN) and machine learning, which suggests that it could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the impact of routing decisions on global aggregate cost, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper presents experiments verifying the performance of the proposed algorithm, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
